	abstract = {The paper aims at investigating how children relate to and make sense of different materials in digital fabrication workshops. Our analysis focuses on how their ways of relating produced different: (1) becoming of the materials, (2) becoming of the to-be-designed project and (3) becoming of the children-as-makers. To this end, we present six vignettes of representative situations encountered in two digital fabrication workshops with primary school children. We used these cases as a foreground to open some initial paths for methodological reflections on digital fabrication in education and its potential as a terrain to work on personal transformative processes. © 2020 Elsevier B.V.},
